one_reviews_text: After launching, I sit watching a spinning particle system forever - feels like a progress spinner perhaps? Nothing I do causes anything to happen. Is this app still supported / running?

At first I was trying to use my finger to select the menu options and felt like I could see where someone might think there was nothing to do, but once I figured out how to select the menu options it made more sense. I look forward to seeing how this develops further!
Tried it , but really doesn't do anything. Kinda of a waste of space. Seriously awful.
review_feedback:
Molando12, 
Thank you very much for trying out the app. As we mentioned in the description, this is a collaboration application that you need a few players to work together. It is a basically a virtual meeting room to replace a telepresence robot (https://static.bhphoto.com/images/images500x500/double_robotics_1011dr_double_2_robot_1479134730000_1288972.jpg)

one_reviews_text: Installed and tried to start. It crashes and you end up back at Oculus Home Screen. I assume a major bug somewhere! Also tried reinstall. No difference. One point I noted is that only 58MB install file size yet it says 2.1GB required. After installing it is still fairly small (180MB or so).
review_feedback: Hi Alan, Thank you very much for trying out our app. and we are sorry that the app crashed on your setting. What kind of hardware setting do you have (CPU, GPU, etc, laptop/PC). Would you please share your crash log from (C:\Program Files\Oculus\Software\Software\inlight-interactive-inlight-spark) to info@inlight.ai?
